# CCOS Project Rules

## UI Components
- ONLY use shadcn/ui components for ALL UI elements. 
  Never create custom components when a shadcn equivalent exists.
- Import from @/components/ui/ (Button, Card, Input, Select, 
  Dialog, Sheet, Table, Tabs, Badge, Avatar, Dropdown, 
  Tooltip, Skeleton, Toast/Sonner, etc.)
- If a shadcn component doesn't exist for a need, 
  compose it from existing shadcn primitives.
- Never install other UI libraries (Material UI, Ant Design, 
  Chakra, Radix directly, Headless UI, etc.)
- Use Lucide React for all icons. Never install other icon packs.

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS only. No inline styles. No CSS modules. 
  No styled-components.
- Use shadcn CSS variables (--primary, --secondary, --muted, 
  --accent, --border, etc.) for all colors.
- Never hardcode hex colors in components — reference 
  Tailwind classes mapped to CSS variables.

## Design Patterns
- Use shadcn Card for all card layouts
- Use shadcn Table for all data tables
- Use shadcn Dialog for modals
- Use shadcn Sheet for side panels
- Use shadcn Tabs for tabbed interfaces
- Use shadcn Form + react-hook-form + zod for all forms
- Use shadcn Select / Combobox for dropdowns
- Use shadcn Badge for status chips and labels
- Use shadcn Skeleton for loading states
- Use Sonner (shadcn toast) for all notifications/toasts
- Use shadcn AlertDialog for confirmations

## i18n
- All user-facing text must come from next-intl translations.
- Never hardcode Arabic or English strings in components.
- Use useTranslations() hook in client components.
- Use getTranslations() in server components.

## Data
- All database queries must filter by tenantId.
- Use Prisma client from @/lib/prisma.
- Use server components for data fetching when possible.
- Use API routes only when client interaction is needed.

## Fonts
- Arabic locale: Cairo
- English locale: Montserrat
- Never use other fonts.

## Direction
- Arabic: dir="rtl"
- English: dir="ltr"
- Use logical CSS properties (ms-, me-, ps-, pe-) 
  instead of left/right when possible.

## Icons
- ONLY use Lucide React icons. These are the shadcn 
  ecosystem icons.
- Import from "lucide-react" package only.
- Never use emoji as icons (no 📋 👥 🗳️ 📝 etc.)
- Never use Heroicons, Font Awesome, React Icons, 
  Material Icons, or any other icon library.
- Never use Unicode symbols or emoji as visual elements.
- Every icon must be a Lucide React component 
  (e.g., <Calendar />, <Users />, <Vote />, 
  <FileText />, <Plus />, <Trash2 />, etc.)

## Bilingual & Direction (CRITICAL)
- Every single page, component, modal, dialog, sheet, 
  toast, empty state, error message, button label, 
  placeholder, table header, and tooltip MUST work 
  in both Arabic and English.
- Never hardcode ANY text string — always use 
  next-intl translations (useTranslations for client, 
  getTranslations for server).
- If you add a new string, add it to BOTH 
  messages/ar.json AND messages/en.json immediately.
- Arabic locale = dir="rtl", English locale = dir="ltr".
- Always use Tailwind logical properties:
  - Use ms-* (margin-inline-start) not ml-*
  - Use me-* (margin-inline-end) not mr-*
  - Use ps-* (padding-inline-start) not pl-*
  - Use pe-* (padding-inline-end) not pr-*
  - Use start-* not left-*
  - Use end-* not right-*
  - Use text-start not text-left
  - Use text-end not text-right
- For flex layouts that should flip in RTL, 
  use flex-row (Tailwind auto-flips with dir).
- Test every component mentally in both directions 
  before writing it.
- Date formatting must respect locale 
  (Arabic numerals + month names for ar).
